article.description: Lenny Daniel scored 18 points and pulled down 13 rebounds as CS Northridge defeated Cal St.-Fullerton 89-65 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Cal State-Fullerton blown out by CS Northridge
article.linkText: Cal State-Fullerton blown out by CS Northridge
article.story: Northridge, Calif. -- Lenny Daniel scored 18 points and pulled down 13 rebounds as CS Northridge defeated Cal St.-Fullerton 89-65 on Saturday night. Vinnie McGhee had 15 points and Aqeel Quinn added 11 for the Matadors (5-12, 2/3 Big West), who shot 56 percent from the field (30 of 54). The Matadors broke open a 17-17 game by outscoring the Titans (6-12, 2-4) 24-8 to take a 41-25 lead at the half. Perry Webster scored 17 points to lead Cal St.-Fullerton, and Jer'Vaughn Johnson added 13 points. Andre Hardy pulled down a game-high 14 rebounds to go with his six points for the Matadors.
